&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for an experienced engineering leader to lead our Desktop Engineering team. This key leadership role requires deep expertise in desktop application development and a strong product focus to deliver innovative AI-powered experiences to our users. You&#39;ll be responsible for building a high-performing engineering team focused on creating elegant, cross-platform desktop applications that put the power of our AI capabilities at users&#39; fingertips.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll lead engineers working with a mix of native and web technologies to create the best possible version of Claude for macOS and Windows, bridging our AI technology with intuitive user interfaces that transform how people engage with advanced language models.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Today, our app is mostly web-based, but we&#39;re heavily investing in native code and deeper integrations into the operating systems. This means your team will work across multiple programming languages and platforms—from Chromium and Electron to C++ and native macOS and Windows APIs. You&#39;ll work closely with engineers, researchers, and product specialists to shape both the technical direction and the team culture from the ground up. This role requires deep expertise in desktop application development, strong product instincts, and a track record of building teams that deliver innovative, cross-platform experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
