&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for an experienced engineering leader to lead our Public Sector Engineering team as we scale Claude across all levels of governments worldwide. This role requires deep expertise in building products that enable governments to deploy advanced AI applications for their most critical operations—from national security to public services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the engineering manager for this team, you will build products and infrastructure at the intersection of cutting-edge AI capabilities and the most demanding deployment environments, from local and federal agencies to international government partnerships. You&#39;d be joining at an inflection point for this team, where we are building out not just the necessary infrastructure, but also AI products based on cutting-edge research to unlock government applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll collaborate closely with product, policy, sales, and applied AI teams to deliver solutions that directly influence how democratic institutions deploy, use, and govern advanced AI systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and lead a high-performing team of engineers focused on public sector AI applications, research, and infrastructure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive delivery of specialized AI applications for governments by developing deep understanding of workflows and data systems&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate very closely with research on AI models for government applications and workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and execute the technical strategy for public sector infrastructure, including architecture decisions for airgapped networks, and government compliance requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner directly with government customers and internal go-to-market teams to translate mission requirements into technical and product roadmaps&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create clarity and technical direction in a fast-moving environment with unique constraints&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
